<br /><p id="bodybold"><a name="FAQ2" id="#FAQ1"></a><FONT FACE="Geneva, Verdana" Size="3"><STRONG>Using the HirePortal</STRONG></FONT><br />
</p>
<ol>
  <li><a name="FAQ7" id="#FAQ7"></a><FONT FACE="Geneva, Verdana" Size="2"><STRONG>What is the HirePortal?</STRONG><br />The HirePortal is a fully-branded, online website that allows Hiring Managers from within your company to communicate their recruitment needs directly with MindField Group.  Using the Portal, you can create new job vacancies, view candidates screened by MindField Group for your job vacancies, hire or reject candidates that MindField Group has presented, access “Live Chat”, and find all training materials related to recruitment.</FONT><br /><br />
  </li>
  <li><a name="FAQ8" id="#FAQ8"></a><FONT FACE="Geneva, Verdana" Size="2"><STRONG>How do I create a new job vacancy using the HirePortal?</STRONG><br /> We invite you to watch out “How to Create a Job” training video.  Alternatively, from any page of the HirePortal, click the <em>Create a Job </em>button on the left-hand side of your screen.  This will take you to a page where you can  edit the job vacancy details. Provide details of the job vacancy you are  looking to fill.  All boxes marked with a  red line are required.  There are a  number of additional boxes and fields that can be filled in as appropriate for  your job vacancy.  Click the <em>Save</em> button to have MindField Group  notified of your new job vacancy.<br /><br />You can also watch our training video on <strong><a href="http://www.screencast.com/users/MindField/folders/Hiring%20Manager%20Portal%20Training%20Videos/media/cfd32569-41d9-400c-b69a-842baad3211b" target="_BLANK">how to create a job opening</a>.</strong></FONT><br /><br />
  </li>
   <li><a name="FAQ15" id="#FAQ15"></a><FONT FACE="Geneva, Verdana" Size="2"><STRONG>How do I post multiple job vacancies as quickly as possible?</STRONG><br /> To quickly create one job vacancy after another, enter all the details for the first job and then click <STRONG><I>Save and New</I></STRONG>.  This will save your current job and bring you right to the screen where you can create a new one.  Alternatively, if you are posting the exact same job vacancy, you can simply duplicate the job.  To learn to do this, see the help topic How do I post an identical job vacancy multiple times using the HirePortal.  </FONT><br /><br />
  </li>
  <li><a name="FAQ16" id="#FAQ16"></a><FONT FACE="Geneva, Verdana" Size="2"><STRONG>How do I post an identical job vacancy multiple times?</STRONG><br />If you need to post the exact same job vacancy more than once, enter all the details for the first job and then click <STRONG><I>Save</I></STRONG>. This will save your current vacancy and bring you right to the screen where you can see the details about the job.  On that screen, click the <STRONG><I>Duplicate</I></STRONG> button and an exact duplicate of that job will be created. Click <STRONG><I>Save</I></STRONG> and repeat if necessary.  </FONT><br /><br />
  </li>
  <li><a name="FAQ9" id="#FAQ9"></a><FONT FACE="Geneva, Verdana" Size="2"><STRONG>How will I know when MindField Group has submitted qualified candidates for my job vacancy?</STRONG> <BR />There are two ways you will know MindField Group has sent candidates:</FONT></li>
  <ol>
    <li><FONT FACE="Geneva, Verdana" Size="2">A Talent Acquisition Specialist will always send  the candidate application package via email to the designated Hiring Manager email inbox.</FONT></li>
    <li><FONT FACE="Geneva, Verdana" Size="2">From any page of the HirePortal, click <em>View Open Jobs </em>on the left-hand side  of your screen.  All open jobs for your  store will be displayed.  Click on the “Job  ID #” associated with the vacancy you want to view candidates for and you will  be brought to a page that displays all of the candidates submitted for that  vacancy.  Select the candidate record by  clicking on their name. </FONT></li>
    <br />
  </ol>
  <li><a name="FAQ10" id="#FAQ10"></a><FONT FACE="Geneva, Verdana" Size="2"><STRONG>I have a walk-in candidate that I feel would be  a great fit for a role at my store.  How  do I ask MindField Group to follow up with this candidate?</STRONG><br />Please create a new job using the HirePortal (see FAQ #2 above).  When creating your job posting, there is a question that asks “Do You Already Have a  Candidate in Mind”.  From the drop down  menu, select “Yes, please phone screen them for us and send if appropriate”.  Include the candidate’s name and phone number  in the space provided.  </FONT><br /><br />
  </li>
  <li><a name="FAQ11" id="#FAQ11"></a><FONT FACE="Geneva, Verdana" Size="2"><STRONG>How do I update MindField Group on the status of a candidate sent to my store?</STRONG><BR />We invite you to view the “How to  Update Candidate Status” training video to learn more about this topic.</FONT></li>
  <ol>
    <li><FONT FACE="Geneva, Verdana" Size="2">In the HirePortal, use the “Search Candidates”box in the upper left-hand corner of your screen to quickly view  or change the status of a candidate.  Type  the candidate’s first and last name into the search bar and click <em>Search Now</em>.</FONT></li>
    <li><FONT FACE="Geneva, Verdana" Size="2">The candidate’s record appears on the next screen - click on the candidate’s  highlighted name.</FONT></li>
    <li><FONT FACE="Geneva, Verdana" Size="2">On the next screen, click <em>Update Candidate  Status</em> to change the candidate’s status to either “Interviewing/Background  Check”, “Hired” or “Rejected”.</FONT></li>
    <li><FONT FACE="Geneva, Verdana" Size="2">If you are rejecting a candidate, you will be asked to provide a reason why the  candidate is being rejected and whether or not they would be suitable for any  other role within your organization. Please include rejection comments in the  open text box if necessary.</FONT></li>
    <li><FONT FACE="Geneva, Verdana" Size="2">Please  note - if there is more than one candidate attached to your vacancy, you will  be required to update the status of all candidates in order to continue.</FONT></li>
  </ol><br />You can also watch our training video on <strong><a href="http://www.screencast.com/users/MindField/folders/Hiring%20Manager%20Portal%20Training%20Videos/media/6db20980-97c4-49ec-8414-1cb0bc1cde48" target="_BLANK">how to update MindField Group</a>.</strong><br /><br />
  <br />
  <li><a name="FAQ12" id="#FAQ12"></a><FONT FACE="Geneva, Verdana" Size="2"><STRONG>I have rejected all candidates MindField Group has  sent for my vacancy.  How do I request  additional candidates?</STRONG></FONT></li>
  <ol>
    <li><FONT FACE="Geneva, Verdana" Size="2">Change status of all candidates submitted for the vacancy to “Rejected” (see FAQ #5  above).  Fill-in the rejection reasons  for all candidates.</FONT></li>
    <li><FONT FACE="Geneva, Verdana" Size="2">You will be asked if you would like to request additional candidates for your  vacancy.  Simply click the empty box next  to “Request More” and this will automatically create a duplicate posting.  MindField Group will then start the search  for two additional candidates for the role, taking into account the rejection  reasons you provided for the previously rejected candidates.</FONT></li>
    <li><FONT FACE="Geneva, Verdana" Size="2">If there is specific feedback you would like to provide MindField Group related to  the rejected candidates, please reach out to the Customer Success Team via “Live  Chat”.  Follow the link to watch our training video on <strong><a href="http://www.screencast.com/users/MindField/folders/Hiring%20Manager%20Portal%20Training%20Videos/media/cd4a37c5-d174-40c9-a2ee-308a5b17a3f0" target="_BLANK">how to use “Live Chat”</a>.</strong></FONT><br /></LI>
        <br />
  </ol>
  <li><a name="FAQ13" id="#FAQ13"></a><FONT FACE="Geneva, Verdana" Size="2"><STRONG>Where can I find training materials and additional  instructions related to the Recruitment Solution provided by MindField Group?</STRONG><BR />In the HirePortal, click the <em>Help</em> tab from the navigation bar along the top of your screen.  Here, you will find all training documents and  important information related to the program, as well as links to all training  videos.</FONT></li>
</ol>
